Utterances: Hello Ms. Walker, I am Jene and will be your nurse today
Hi.
What brings you in today?
I was having trouble with the pain from my cancer... I just couldn't take it anymore at home.
Can you tell me where you are?
I'm in the hospital.
Have you had anything to drink recently? (Clarified to Have you drank anything today?.)
I had a few sips of ginger ale earlier, but that's about it. (Clarified to if I drank anything today.)
are you in pain when you urinate>?
No, there's no burning or pain there.
when is the last time you ate?
Let's see, I had a few bites of yogurt last night before bed... I think that was the last time I had anything.
Do you have a preference for hospice care?

I want to allow things to take their course . . . it's time for me to stop fighting and just enjoy the time I have left in what little ways I can. My husband and I have chosen an assisted living residence near my home where I'll go for hospice care. I have been told that they can help me with the pain there .  . . and it's close enough that my husband can be with me.
Do you have any advanced directives?
Yes, all my affairs should be in order.
when did the pain begin?
I've been in some pain for a long time, but it reached an unbearable level two days ago.
where us the pain located? (Clarified to Where is the pain?.)
Well, everywhere really . . . These past days I've felt it mostly in my ribs and legs but even my bones hurt. (Clarified to where it hurts.)
can you describe your pain?
I can feel it all over my body . . . It's a sharp pain in my bones, my legs, and my ribs. It's been getting much worse over the past two days.
what aggravates the pain?
Nothing makes the pain worse, nothing makes it better. It's just constant and relentless.
what are some relieving factors for your pain?
I took my pain pills at home but nothing fully gets rid of the pain, really... I'm not ungrateful for what you all have done for me, I can just still feel it there, through the medication.
What is the severity of the pain?
It's better now than before, but I can still feel it there.
Do you have any allergies?
Well, I don't have allergies to anything but penicillin. I told them right when I arrived.
Have you followed up on your penicillin allergy?
As in, followed up with a doctor? I have not. I haven't felt the need to.
do you have any home medications?
I take two types of morphine at home every day and I also manage my hypertension with Hyzaar.
tell me about the long-acting morphine
I've been taking morphine for about six months. That's when the cancer had spread to my bones and the pain was intensifying.
have you followed up with the doctor about your morphine? (No matching questions found.)
do you have a history of substance user?
No, I do not.
do you have any problems with your head?
My head feels just fine, that's not where I'm having the pain.
do you have any problems with your respiratory?
No, I don't have any breathing difficulties.
do you have any cardiac problems?
No, I've never had heart trouble.
do you have any gastrointestinal problems?
Well, I've been getting pain in my stomach and I've been a bit constipated as well. Which I think is why I feel so full and bloated.
has anything been done for your constipation? (No matching questions found.)
has anyone followed up on the constipation? (No matching questions found.)
do you have any neurological problems?
Yes, I've been feeling quite weak lately.
do you have any psychological problems?
No, not specifically . . . I have been feeling somewhat anxious lately though.
do you have depression?
I have my ups and downs. Nothing so down I'd call depression, though.
how is your living environment?

I'm living with my husband in our home. I'm happy there still, all the familiar surroundings, visits from our friends . . . but if the pain is going to be as bad as this morning from now on, I'm not sure what I can do about it at home.
do you feel safe at home?
Of course, I've never felt threatened at home.
who helps you bathe? (Clarified to Do you rely on other people to help you bathe?.)

Yes, I can't quite bathe on my own now. My husband has been helping me when I need to. We also have a shower bench that I sit on so I don't have to worry about falling. (Clarified to if I rely on people to help me bathe.)
do you rely on help to get dressed? (Clarified to Are you able to dress yourself?.)
I don't have any trouble dressing myself. (Clarified to if I can dress myself without problems.)
do you have trouble transferring?
Well, I have the most trouble getting up from any sort of lying position, so I spend most of my time in bed. My husband usually gives me a hand when I need to get up.
do you have continence?
Yes, I haven't had any accidents.
do you eat independently?
Yes, I haven't gotten to that point yet and hopefully won't have to ever worry about having someone feed me.
what are your sleeping habits?
I'll take my medication before bed generally and just try to get what sleep I can. My quality of sleep has been quite poor lately though.
do you experience confusion?
No, I'm not confused right now. This morning the pain was making it a bit hard to think but I'm all here now.
do you have skin breakdown?
I wouldn't call it much of a problem but my skin has been feeling thinner than normal.
have you had any changes in weight?
Yes, I've lost 20 pounds or so in the past two months.
do you have any dental problems?
No, I don't have any problems with my mouth, jaw, or teeth.
have you had a change in your appetite?
My appetite has been rather small lately, I haven't been eating too much for the last months.
tell me about your social activity

Raymond and I have a nice group of families from the church who we see pretty regularly. They've really been great to us and have lifted quite a lot of weight from our shoulders. It's been difficult to see them with my pain as of late though . . .
what is your perception of health?
I'd say my health is poor in general. I'm quite aware of the situation I'm in.
are you tired?
I've been feeling tired all of the time lately.
have you been to the emergency room ?
Yes, I came in this morning.
recent hospital stays? (Clarified to When was your last hospitalization?.)
Well, I haven't been hospitalized for the past three months, but I had some cancer treatments I underwent around three months ago. (Clarified to when the last time I was hospitalized was.)
thank you for that. I am sorry your in pain.
Thank you for saying that. Really.
